Content-Type: text/plain;
	charset=&quot;US-ASCII&quot;
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Thanks Misty.  I appreciate you and the others keeping an ear for their
names.  Does experimenting at the same time everyday make any difference to
help make connections?

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Misty Dawn
Sent: Wednesday, November 28, 2007 4:15 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Re: New file uploaded to EVP-ITC



I wish you luck Kristin. It helps to work with others sometimes others will
get messages to pass on. If your sis is willing perhaps she could record
with you too sometimes. Theres a variety of methods you can do there at
home. With crossing sometimes theres a time barrier on this side, for us it
seems to be either right away when they connect or long after. I am not sure
why that is. I only know that for them time has no meaning. Often they say
things months or years ahead of &quot;time&quot; or I just dont get it until much
later down the road. 



They are welcome to speak in my sessions if they wish to and I am sure
others here feel the same. So they will have many moments in &quot;time&quot; to
choose from to come thru. If I hear those names I&#39;ll be sure and forward it
on. Many names pass thru here. I dont know them but I try to post some of
them just in case its for others. Im unable to post all of my files because
I have very little free time. 



Let me just say that as a mom with kids, you only need a good half hour to
record a couple minutes (set limits...no more than 3 minutes, but 30 seconds
will do fine usually) then spend the rest of the half hour analyzing your
files. Try to record often and that helps you strengthen the connection on
your end as well as thiers. Once the connection is made, you may find that
others give you answers to questions you have about them even if they are
not ready to speak to us themselves. So maybe once the kids are in bed, and
all is quiet in the house, you will find 30 minutes to research. If one
method isnt working for you try one of the others you may get better results
to get you started down the path.



Misty

Kristin Morris &lt;ckmorris95@...&gt; wrote:

Misty - this gives me hope.  I am so new to this and not technical in the
least.  I wish I had 24 hours a day to dedicate to ITC but I have small
children and they seem to take all my time.  I am hoping to find a few hours
to modify that RS and really begin my attempts.  I am very grateful that
this low tech idea was passed onto to us!  Just 3 weeks ago I too lost my
niece (17yrs) and nephew (14yrs) to a car accident.  Aly, my niece died on
impact, but her brother Ryan hung on for 4 more days and I was there with my
sister (his mom) and his dad when they ended life support.  I don&#39;t know if
it is too soon.. but what a wonderful gift I could give my sister if I could
capture their voices and let her know that her two children are still with
us.

k



  _____  


From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Misty Dawn
Sent: Wednesday, November 28, 2007 1:36 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: New file uploaded to EVP-ITC

Glad she made it thru but sorry it had to be this way. I understand how that
feels. Yes on the training part too, I have gotten that quite often over the
years when new spirits begin to speak sometimes the others help them or even
speak for them if they arent getting across clearly. Sometimes its very
detailed instructions that blow my mind. But it is interesting to listen to
thier conversations there. 

I also used to notice that sometimes when I would try a new method it would
be almost as if my close contacts would go to another broadcasting station,
go in, introduce themselves and announce they were there to speak to me or
the relation to me then take over the session. Sometimes I think different
methods invite new contacts/entities. However many of the contacts remain
the same and will use any method I choose. 

Losing so many people on this side only strengthens the bonds to that side
more. Of that I have no doubt. It&#39;s the ties that bind. Very true statement.
For those who havent experienced loss its a bit of a different experience
overall. Theres nothing that can compare to hearing a voice thats been dead
for so long or that you thought you would never hear again in this lifetime.
Some of you know how that feels. It just hits such a high note that it
resonates thru your spirit sometimes. In my case I have too many best
friends, loved ones, relations who went before me and did keep thier promise
to stay in touch whatever it took. 

Only when we were all making those promises so many years ago we were just
saying it more for the joke of it rather than the reality of it. One by one
they all crossed over, and one by one they have kept thier promises. 

So, that being said

&quot;If I die before you die I&#39;m coming back to haunt you all&quot;

  &lt;http://us.i1.yimg.com/us.yimg.com/i/mesg/tsmileys2/03.gif&gt; 

Misty


Steve Hultay &lt;urkel23@...&gt; wrote:

Yeah, since i start using the Radio Shack radios i have been getting 
full sentence conversations with them. I&#39;ve been trying to contact 
my ex-girlfriend that passed last year at 29. That does sound like 
her voice, she has been coming through since Sunday night and i 
actually heard them through the radio telling her to talk and she 
said &quot;Hi Steve&quot;. They were like training her to use the radio, 
pretty weird stuff but it was good to hear from her in her own 
voice. The response time is remarkable with these radios, they seem 
to answer right away very &quot;frank&#39;s box&quot;-like. These will keep me 
occupied while i wait for #27---the #13 replacement. I&#39;m really 
excited about that one, it may be the one to live up to for all 
future boxes. I&#39;m sure Frank could buy a radio shack box and add a 
sound chamber, that would probably really enhance the voices. These 
other boxes and radios are great, but there&#39;s only one Frank&#39;s Box 
for all others to try to live up to. I don&#39;t think a 10 Minute mod 
on a $25 dollar radio will ever replace the time and effort frank 
puts into his boxes. But anybody can try these radios and that&#39;s 
what is important, but without Frank there would have been no 
advancement in ITC. Someone had to break the ground work.

-Steve H.

